The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for multivariate time series prediction, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The proposed architecture involves transforming the original time series into a higher order tensor, which is a technique commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also mentions the use of convolutional kernels, which are commonly used in deep learning for image and signal processing (cs.CV, cs.NE). Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of existing methods and the need for scalable and efficient solutions, which are topics commonly discussed in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) communities. Finally, the paper presents experimental results and a sensitivity analysis, which are common practices in the field of machine learning and signal processing (cs.SI).
